def_cn: 过于高雅的;过于高贵的;脱离现实生活的
def_en: If you talk about the rarefied atmosphere of a place or institution, you are expressing your disapproval of it, because it has a special social or academic status that makes it very different from ordinary life.

def_cn: （空气）稀薄的，含氧量少的
def_en: Rarefied air is air that does not contain much oxygen, for example in mountain areas.
